      • registerJsCategoryExtensions

        void registerJsCategoryExtensions(String bundleName,
                                  Map<String,List<String>> resources)
                           throws ConcatenatedResourceStoreException
        Extend some of the JavaScript categories with JavaScript files of a plugin. This method should usually only be called if adding the JavaScript files depends on some condition like the availability of a service.
        Parameters:
        bundleName - the name of the bundle for which the resources should be added
        resources - mapping from category name to a list of resources
        Throws:
        ConcatenatedResourceStoreException - in case a category could not be updated
